-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
SUMMARY (human-readable; not a substitute for the full legal code)
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

You are free to:

  * Share  — copy and redistribute the material in any medium or format.
  * Adapt  — remix, transform, and build upon the material.

The licensor cannot revoke these freedoms as long as you follow the license
terms.

Under the following terms:

  * Attribution (BY) — You must give appropriate credit, provide a link to the
    license, and indicate if changes were made. You may do so in any reasonable
    manner, but not in any way that suggests the licensor endorses you or your
    use.

  * NonCommercial (NC) — You may not use the material for commercial purposes.
    Creative Commons defines noncommercial use as use that is "not primarily
    intended for or directed towards commercial advantage or monetary
    compensation."

  * ShareAlike (SA) — If you remix, transform, or build upon the material, you
    must distribute your contributions under the same license as the original.

  * No additional restrictions — You may not apply legal terms or technological
    measures that legally restrict others from doing anything the license
    permits.

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
NOTES
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

This license is "source-available" rather than OSI-"open source": the OSI Open
Source Definition does not permit restrictions on commercial use, so the
NonCommercial term places this outside that definition. Creative Commons also
advises against using CC licenses for software, because they do not address
patent rights or distinguish source code from object code. These notes are
informational and are not legal advice.

To bundle the complete legal code in this file, append the official plaintext
from: https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/4.0/legalcode.txt
